article.description: Toni Young had 20 points and 10 rebounds, and led six Oklahoma State players scoring in double figures Friday night as the 23rd-ranked Cowgirls routed Cal Poly 90-59.
article.headline: Young's double-double powers No. 23 Okla. St. by Cal Poly
article.linkText: Young's double-double powers No. 23 Okla. St.
article.story:
STILLWATER, Okla. -- Toni Young had 20 points and 10 rebounds, and led six Oklahoma State scorers in double figures Friday night as the 23rd-ranked Cowgirls routed Cal Poly 90-59.

Liz Donohoe scored 16 points, Brittney Martin scored 15, Tiffany Bias scored 12 and Lindsey Keller and Kendra Suttles added 10 points apiece for Oklahoma State, which pulled away after the first 10 minutes in its season opener.

Molly Schlemer had 21 points and 12 rebounds for Cal Poly. The Mustangs trailed 18-17 with 11 minutes left in the first half, but the Cowgirls scored 12 of the next 14 points in the game and opened up a 48-28 halftime lead.
